# Bias-Variance Tradeoff

This notebook discusses the concepts of bias and variance and how they impact model performance in machine learning.

## Bias
Bias refers to the error due to overly simplistic assumptions in the learning algorithm. A model with high bias tends to underfit the data.

## Variance
Variance refers to the error due to excessive complexity in the learning algorithm. A model with high variance tends to overfit the data.

## Bias-Variance Tradeoff
The tradeoff between bias and variance is a fundamental problem in supervised learning. Reducing bias typically increases variance and vice versa.

## Conclusion
Understanding the bias-variance tradeoff is essential for building effective machine learning models.